social_posts.post_text: These dogs have a lot of patience for me and my holiday bs🤣🎅

Procrastination this year means the holiday card will be digital.. but these festive shoes, Rob’s handsomeness and the talent of @chelsaegracephotography made it worth doing still ❤️🎄plus it was fun to shop for more fun white dresses 💃🏼

Did I apply this shittily? Yes, but I’m a bright lipstick newbie 💄 Trying out Chanel’s rouge coco flash in shade 152 (shake.) Love the high shine and how it just glides on. Surprisingly, I like the shade of red I picked for myself online.

With just 7 hours in Paris, visiting Celine to buy a bag was on our short itinerary💃🏼 I knew the prices would be lower plus a tax refund when you leave the country.

I had been eyeing the classic triomphe bag and bucket 16 and the triomphe bag is $3950 USD PLUS tax, but 3000 euros in France ($3260 dollars including tax.) The bucket bag was 2100 euros ($2,284 USD) but in US it would cost $2750 USD plus tax. 

I bought the bucket bag and a small belt, two classic pieces I’ll wear forever and associate with my day in Paris 🤗

Plus, I saved an extra $300 with the VAT refund after I went through customs at the train station (they make it super easy, just scan a barcode on your receipt.)
Went out until 8:30 pm for a gala 💃🏼 obv had to document wearing a dressier dress

Some snaps from London and Paris 🖤 loved my first trip abroad so much, I already booked our honeymoon trip to Amsterdam, Antwerp and back to Paris this summer 👩‍❤️‍👨 if anyone has recs for any of these cities, I’m all ears!
The pictures I choose to share of me on my birthday vs what friends/family share 💀 #thisis37
Weekend highlights ❤️🐶☕️ Got out and about more this weekend than usual but also plenty of couch cuddles with the dogs and binge watching vanderpump rules 👀

Love a late night out until 8 pm 👵🏻🥂 checked out bubbly bar Pursuit of Happiness in Grand Rapids yesterday and it did not disappoint (@jasperwcunningham always picks the best spots no matter where we are.) Ordered a glass of Prosecco before we headed around the corner to Terra for dinner 🍕
So long, April 👋🏻 some good mems ❤️

I’m in recovery mode from one of the most fun weekends I’ve ever had all because of these amazing friends of mine. These friendships began from a mix of elementary, high school, college and beyond and you know they’re true friends when they embrace your quirks, roast you lovingly 💀 and also share the same poop humor 🤣

A little behind the scenes of a portrait session with one of my good friends @hayschraub and super into my photographer fit of the day 💃🏼 Wearing this gifted @karen_millen blazer paired with a biker short bodysuit.
Spent the last week up north 🌊 A long weekend on Hubbard Lake and a long week on Mackinac Island 🤣 Glad to rest up at home the next week before we head up north for the wedding ❤️

Rob participating/humoring me with this reel 👩‍❤️‍👨 we went on our own adventures this afternoon, rob went to the louvre and I went shopping and exploring le Marais at my fast walking pace 😎 and we ended the evening with a car tour of the city 🚘

Souvenirs from Paris (mostly!)

Celine bucket 16 bag in tan (picked up for my friend!) along with the a tan Celine belt from the Celine shop on Avenue Montaigne. This location is spacious compared to the others and not chaotically busy in my opinion. I also snagged a Celine teen triomphe bag in the airport store on my way home. 

Souvenirs were bought mostly from the shops along Rue de Rivoli near Angelina and across the street from Jardin des Tuileries. I got an ashtray for my chain smoking parents, an assortment of magnets and Eiffel Tower trinkets for family members and a tote. Lots of cute tote options along here. We also visited the magnificent Galeries Lafayette for the rooftop view of the city and shopped on the way up and the last floor is all souvenirs where I found a chic tote and so many books and such but no space in my carry on! 

City Pharma is the iconic pharmacy for shopping skincare and their staff is incredibly helpful and they have a huge selection but it’s too nuts for me with so many people it’s hard to even move around. You can find the same products for the most part at all the smaller pharmacies and even Monoprix and that’s where I picked up Avene and Caudalie products. I also grabbed snacks and treats as souvenirs from Monoprix! Lots of souvenirs missing but you get the idea, more magnets, a couple more skincare products that were rebuys of products I got back in January when I was here and treats like stroopwaffles were brought home 🥰

Some Paris moments ✨ 

- @2cvparistour_com tour (one hour tour but would book a longer tour next time! Customized to what we wanted to see and pick up from our hotel)
-Galeries Lafayette, a century-old department store with an art nouveau glass dome, and stunning city views on the rooftop, plus shopping including a souvenir shop, secondhand/vintage clothing, etc. 
-Wandering the first arr (stayed in this area at Melia Vendome) visited Jardin de Tuileries and the Louvre, sixth arr for breakfast at the iconic Les Deux Magots, Le Bon Marche department store shopping and Jardin du Luxembourg, Le Marais (wish we had more time for the vintage shopping here!) More shared on my blog for Paris and Amsterdam ❤️

Choosing a new coffee table felt like a daunting task for me, a person who orders online without checking measurements and overall lacks the concept of space and size. I wanted a statement coffee table, something that would add some sophistication and that wow factor, but also fit the space better.

I’ve worked with @bradlyshg to purchase furniture in the past for two homes and knew I could trust Bradly to source beautiful options that would complement the space. His process includes a consultation with a home visit followed by an in-store appointment where he’ll present options he believes works with your style and the size of the space. It didn’t take me long to narrow it down to this faux marble coffee table so then he ordered it, I paid the deposit and the rest once it was ready to be delivered (for free) to my home ❤️ 

It absolutely elevates this living room and pulls everything together #ad #shoplocal
